Gumby's Pizza - Columbia, MO

I was working in Columbia last week when a few coworkers suggested we stop by Gumby's Pizza for lunch. Located downtown near the Mizzou campus, Gumby's is a well-known local spot that's popular with students and residents alike. As with most downtown areas, parking can be a bit of a challenge, so plan accordingly.

At first glance, the restaurant looks small from the outside, but once you step inside, you'll find it surprisingly spacious. When you walk in, you're greeted by specials posted throughout the entrance area. We arrived right around noon and, to our surprise, we were the only group dining at that time.

Orders are placed at the counter, where we were helped by a woman who was absolutely fantastic--friendly, patient, and accommodating, especially considering that several people in our group were visiting for the first time. After ordering, you can choose to sit at a booth, high-top table, or at the bar. The atmosphere is casual and inviting, with TVs throughout, a music machine, and even a pool table for entertainment.
Since I'm currently following a fasting diet and skip breakfast and lunch, I ordered my meal to go so I could enjoy it for dinner. Having had plenty of pizza the night before at Shakespeare's, I decided to switch things up. I went with a pound of boneless wings--half buffalo, half mango habanero--and added a side of beef toasted ravioli. One of our local coworkers also ordered the XL cheese bread for the table, and I can confidently say, based on both this visit and past experiences, it's easily in my top three for cheese bread anywhere. Everyone in our group was happy with their food, from the pizzas to the other menu items.

Overall, Gumby's is a spot l'll continue to visit whenever I'm in Columbia. Great service, solid food, and a laid-back vibe make it a go-to for a casual meal downtown.

I asked Kathy her recommendation. Before I could even finish my question, ‚ÄúThe Stoner‚Äù, cut me off. Pepperoni, bacon, French fries, and I think cheese curds?! D-licious!!! Great location, fun atmosphere and super friendly staff. Highly recommend Gumby‚Äôs!

I ordered a supreme pizza off door dash. When I opened the box and saw a cheese pizza, I was really mad. When I checked the label I saw "supreme pizza, no pepperoni, no sausage, no onions, no green peppers" and went WTH? I checked the app and sure enough, I had managed to order a supreme pizza and yet unchecked all the toppings. As mad as I was at myself, I have to hand it to Gumby's for fully supporting and not even questioning the crazy order that costs more than a cheese pizza, yet is just a cheese pizza.  What's the opposite of a bargain hunter? That's me!

5 stars for supporting your customers' stated wishes, no matter how insane.
